               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18390708-name-579" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-579" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-579" type="surname" value="WENTWORTH"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18390708-name-579" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WENTWORTH</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in the parish of St. George-the-Martyr. Between four and five o'clock yesterday morning, my wife awoke me, and I heard some one going down stairs out of the room—I had left the articles mentioned in the room—I got up, ran down, and found the clothes on the stairs—I looked about, but could not find any person—in half an hour, I looked up the kitchen chimney, and found the prisoner there without his shoes—I pulled him down—I did not find any thing on him—the clothes were on the stair-case, with a pair of shoes, which I believe belonged to the prisoner—his hat I found under my bed.</p>
